{
  "title": "About Rcngraph Plugin",
  "story": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "f3a8d291b4c56e17",
      "text": "The Rcngraph plugin opens the RCN Graph Diagramming Tool in a full popup window linked to the wiki lineup. Supported diagram types: Causal Loop (CLD), Influence (EIP), Object-Process (OPM), Viable System (VSM), and Neighbourhood Risk Management (NRM)."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "2e7c9f04a3b8d651",
      "text": "Create an item using the factory. Click **Open Graph Tool ↗** to open the tool. Use **→ Item** to save the diagram as an SVG preview back into the wiki item. Use **→ Wiki** to send the diagram to the lineup as a ghost page with node labels as internal wiki links. The wiki page title is passed to the tool as the default diagram name."
    },
    {
      "type": "rcngraph",
      "id": "8d4e2a7f1c9b3065",
      "text": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "4b6f8e3d9c2a1705",
      "text": "Developed by Marc Pierson with Claude Sonnet 4.6 (Anthropic) for the ReLocalize Creativity Network. Source: [[https://github.com/marpie1/wiki-plugin-rcngraph]]. Published on npm as wiki-plugin-rcngraph."
    }
  ],
